UNITED STATES of America, Appellant, v. Albert L. SMITH, Appellee. No. 9037. Circuit Court of Appeals, Ninth Circuit. Nov. 28, 1938. Ben Harris, U. S. Atty., and Ernest D. Fooks and Attilio DiGirolamo, Attys., Department of Justice, all of Los Angeles, Cal. Chenoweth & Whitehead, of Los Angeles, Cal., for appellee.

Before GARRECHT, HANEY, and STEPHENS, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

Upon stipulation of counsel for respective parties, ordered appeal dismissed, that a judgment of dismissal be filed and entered accordingly, and that the mandate of this court in this cause issue forthwith.
